node.text:
In recognition of CROWN Day, Phenomenal produced this video in collaboration with @haydenfive and @jjxanderson to celebrate owning your crown and passing it to the next generation.

What is CROWN Day? The CROWN Act ensures protection against race-based hairstyle discrimination in the workplace and public schools. The CROWN Coalition, which advocates for the passage of CROWN Act legislation nationwide, has declared July 3 to be "CROWN Day."

Through our CROWN initiative, Phenomenal is encouraging Black women to reclaim our hairstory and celebrate our crowns. We hope to help shift culture and dialogue around natural and textured hair, beyond just anti-discrimination, to achieve respect and freedom — to express ourselves unapologetically; to wear our hair however we choose, wherever we are.

Thank you to this dream team: director @jjxanderson DP/cinematographer @nataliamoscoso 1stAC @chowingdownchow on-set photography @hrdwrkerxtito writer @yazminmonetwatkins talent @tiffanygouche @naimajoy @amyelisajackson @joysimmonsdivadoc @alexisnrdavidson @bephie
